00:30:23.650 --> 00:30:27.210
the same model that went over
into the White House lawn

00:30:27.210 --> 00:30:30.580
that banned drone flying in
the D.C. area for some time.

00:30:30.580 --> 00:30:32.110
[INAUDIBLE] at a certain radius.

00:30:32.110 --> 00:30:34.690
That we've been using this
to drive elephants out

00:30:34.690 --> 00:30:35.500
of croplands.

00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:38.680
And the litmus test is
driving them out at night

00:30:38.680 --> 00:30:40.810
when they're already in
the maize fields feeding.

00:30:40.810 --> 00:30:42.970
Because just during the
daytime like this is great,

00:30:42.970 --> 00:30:46.739
but the real test is when
they're destroying crops.

00:30:46.739 --> 00:30:48.280
The results are sort
of unbelievable.

00:30:48.280 --> 00:30:50.690
As a scientist,
we've done 51 trials.

00:30:50.690 --> 00:30:52.740
And we've had 100% success rate.

00:30:52.740 --> 00:30:55.420
Within 20 seconds, the
elephants turn and run.

00:30:55.420 --> 00:30:57.340
And we have great
videos of-- which

00:30:57.340 --> 00:31:00.310
I won't show now, but of
herds being driven away back

00:31:00.310 --> 00:31:02.930
into a national park
over several kilometers

00:31:02.930 --> 00:31:05.550
by this little, tiny $500 drone.

00:31:05.550 --> 00:31:08.060
If the drones themselves
don't scare them, attach

00:31:08.060 --> 00:31:10.880
the very high-tech device
at the bottom of the drone

00:31:10.880 --> 00:31:13.970
is a plastic bag full of chili
powder with holes poked in it.

00:31:13.970 --> 00:31:16.700
And we just jiggle the drone
and out comes the chili powder.

00:31:16.700 --> 00:31:18.167
And they hate the
smell of chili.

00:31:18.167 --> 00:31:19.250
And that drives them away.

00:31:19.250 --> 00:31:20.890
We haven't had to use that yet.

00:31:20.890 --> 00:31:23.530
But the reason we think
this is so effective

00:31:23.530 --> 00:31:26.140
is that the propellers
make a sound very

00:31:26.140 --> 00:31:29.500
similar to the frequency of
swarming angry bees or hornets.

00:31:29.500 --> 00:31:31.730
And elephants have this
out-sized fear of bees.

00:31:31.730 --> 00:31:33.200
It's not mice they're scared of.

00:31:33.200 --> 00:31:34.600
It's bees.

00:31:34.600 --> 00:31:36.780
Maybe they're afraid
they'll fly up their trunks

00:31:36.780 --> 00:31:39.600
or in their ears, but I think
this is genetically hardwired.

00:31:39.600 --> 00:31:41.930
We don't think they're going
to get habituated to this,

00:31:41.930 --> 00:31:42.840
but we'll see.

00:31:42.840 --> 00:31:45.630
But we've done this now for
two different crop seasons.

00:31:45.630 --> 00:31:47.160
And it's we're incredibly well.

00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:50.430
So we're now trying to scale
this to other parts of Africa.

00:31:50.430 --> 00:31:52.420
Where we're going
next in two more weeks

00:31:52.420 --> 00:31:54.500
is to Tsavo National Park.

00:31:54.500 --> 00:31:57.780
He mentioned, Mark [? Gos, ?]
the Sheldrick Trust.

00:31:57.780 --> 00:31:59.770
We're working with
them to deploy

00:31:59.770 --> 00:32:01.340
these anti-poaching devices.

00:32:01.340 --> 00:32:04.590
So one of the
things-- as I said,

00:32:04.590 --> 00:32:07.087
we have to stop poachers
before they kill.

00:32:07.087 --> 00:32:09.420
All of the devices, the camera
traps that are out there.

00:32:09.420 --> 00:32:11.860
These kind of big, bulky boxes
that are above the ground.

00:32:11.860 --> 00:32:14.180
They can be camouflaged,
but sharp-eyed poachers

00:32:14.180 --> 00:32:15.750
can find them and smash them.

00:32:15.750 --> 00:32:17.420
Elephants will smash them.

00:32:17.420 --> 00:32:20.150
Our device is a
little, tiny unit

00:32:20.150 --> 00:32:21.340
that is simply above ground.

00:32:21.340 --> 00:32:23.756
And the rest of it is hidden
away either underground or up

00:32:23.756 --> 00:32:24.520
in the tree.

00:32:24.520 --> 00:32:27.670
But this can be hidden in a
fake vine in a rain forest.

00:32:27.670 --> 00:32:29.980
Or you'll see in a
second, where we do it.

00:32:29.980 --> 00:32:32.030
And it sends an
image of the poacher.

00:32:32.030 --> 00:32:33.890
It has human detection
algorithms in it.

00:32:33.890 --> 00:32:36.490
And sends out either
satellite, cell,

00:32:36.490 --> 00:32:42.270
or through a long-range radio
frequency to the headquarters.

00:32:42.270 --> 00:32:43.940
This is actually
smaller than this now,

00:32:43.940 --> 00:32:45.402
but this was the
first prototype.

00:32:45.402 --> 00:32:46.610
This is just the camera head.

00:32:46.610 --> 00:32:49.810
It's as big as your thumb
that sits above ground,

00:32:49.810 --> 00:32:51.590
but that's cryptic and hidden.

00:32:51.590 --> 00:32:54.050
And then, there's a
passive infrared beam here.

00:32:54.050 --> 00:32:56.330
It's broken, wakes
up the camera.

00:32:56.330 --> 00:33:00.060
It takes the pictures,
and then sends them all.

00:33:00.060 --> 00:33:02.640
Only those though,
that are humans

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:05.030
so that we save
energy and battery

00:33:05.030 --> 00:33:06.900
life of not just
sending branches,

00:33:06.900 --> 00:33:10.980
or birds, or other creatures.

00:33:10.980 --> 00:33:12.960
So I'm going to
ask you now, where

00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:16.354
do you think that
camera head is hidden?

